TY  - JOUR
T1  - Social Capital: Maturation of a Field of Research
AU  - Kwon, Seok-Woo
AU  - Adler, Paul S.
Y1  - 2014/10/01
PY  - 2014
DA  - 2014/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2014.0210
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2014.0210
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 412
EP  - 422
VL  - 39
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Over the past decade social capital has matured from a concept into a field of research. We identify some of the main theoretical developments over this period and point to some areas where further work appears warranted. We argue that the basic social capital thesis has now been widely accepted across a range of disciplines and fields, and that research is therefore naturally shifting toward more specific aspects and mechanisms.
AB  - Over the past decade social capital has matured from a concept into a field of research. We identify some of the main theoretical developments over this period and point to some areas where further work appears warranted. We argue that the basic social capital thesis has now been widely accepted across a range of disciplines and fields, and that research is therefore naturally shifting toward more specific aspects and mechanisms.
